  "texts": [
    "The planning process unfolds as follows:1) The LLMs brainstorm all workable and distinct plans based on the current scenario and goal.",
    "2) For each of the proposed plans, the LLMs will evaluate the potential of them, consider their pros and cons, implementation difficulty, potential challenges and then assign safety, efficiency score from 0 to 10 to each option based on these factors.",
    "3) Based on the evaluations and scenarios, rank the plans.",
    "4) A singular plan is selected to guide driving decisions.",
    "If there is a pre-existing plan, the LLM evaluates other vehicles' intentions from the multi-agent interaction module."
  ],
